        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 11:34AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1133 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Marathon, or 30 miles east of Alpine, moving east
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marathon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
